The paper deals with estimation theory, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). It also involves signal processing (cs.SP) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The use of a basis expansion model (BEM) suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.MM), and the derivation of closed-form expressions for the mean-squared error (MSE) and signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) suggests a connection to mathematical optimization (cs.LG).
